trans-unit.source:
Returns a <code>BigDecimal</code> which is equivalent to this one with the decimal point moved <code>n</code> places to the left. If <code>n</code> is non-negative, the call merely adds <code>n</code> to the scale. If <code>n</code> is negative, the call is equivalent to <code>movePointRight(-n)</code>. The <code>BigDecimal</code> returned by this call has value <code>(this &times;
 10<sup>-n</sup>)</code> and scale <code>max(this.scale()+n,
 0)</code>.

Returns a <code>BigDecimal</code> whose value is <code>(this &times;
 multiplicand)</code>, and whose scale is <code>(this.scale() +
 multiplicand.scale())</code>.
